			<outline text="April 20" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 13:03:18 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="20">
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xwtdhWltSIg&quot;&gt;Losing My Religion&lt;/a&gt;." created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 22:04:08 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="BTW, my plan is to hook &quot;RSS&quot; up to any protocol people come up with. And when I say RSS, I mean all flavors including RDF and Atom. I don't just have advice for other people, sometimes I give myself advice too. I think it's time to love RSS again. :heart:" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 17:21:34 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I adore the current &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Jeopardy/status/1516612723471224838&quot;&gt;Jeopardy champion Mattea Roach&lt;/a&gt;. Actually I adore them all. They are amazing people. Not only do they have great memory, but think about all the things they know. I also think &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Jennings&quot;&gt;Ken Jennings&lt;/a&gt; is the obvious best choice to be the Jeopardy host because he's such a great Jeopardy player, is immersed in all aspects of the game and he really connects with the players, and therefore the fans at home. They are all such wonderful unabashed nerds. I've been watching the show since I was a kid, when &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art_Fleming&quot;&gt;Art Fleming&lt;/a&gt; was the host, when I watched it with my mom. " created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 13:07:42 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/20/earlyJeopardyBoard.png"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/phonetonote/status/1516538831528468490&quot;&gt;Yes&lt;/a&gt;, I do edit my JavaScript code in an &lt;a href=&quot;http://home.opml.org/&quot;&gt;outliner&lt;/a&gt;. A few years ago I started including the OPML source in my GitHub projects. Look for source.opml. It has the source for all the files in the project in one file. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/opmlPackage&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 14:23:43 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="We're curing ourselves from Covid the way people who smoke while they quit smoking aren't actually quitting. To quit, you stop. If you take your masks off, that's like buying a pack of cigarettes, and having one or two and then finishing the pack and then getting another. I speak as an ex-smoker for over 30 years. I had all kinds of plans for quitting, but the only way to do it is to quit. We'll never get out of the Covid hole until &lt;i&gt;all of us&lt;/i&gt; commit to it and then follow through. Otherwise it's going to continue to be a lingering tragedy. " created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 17:36:55 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I'm going to continue to wear a mask when I go out in public. My face feels naked without it. The other day I went into the supermarket without a mask and had to go back out to the car to get one. In that moment I got to think about why I wear a mask even when others aren't. It's because I want to send a message to my fellow shoppers that I care about their health. I was raised to be a considerate person. So many people were raised to be self-centered and pissy. I never want to see myself that way. Anyway it was really annoying how quickly the airlines took down their mask requirements. I suggest if you want to make your feelings known to them, stop flying until they bring the mandates back." created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 13:03:19 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/20/elves.png"/>
				<outline text="&quot;Tactical&quot; nuclear weapon is an idea like &quot;neo&quot; Nazi. A distinction without a difference." created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 20:22:45 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Jeopardy!" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 13:15:52 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Jeopardy host &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art_Fleming&quot;&gt;Art Fleming&lt;/a&gt; with contestants." created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 13:16:01 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/20/jeopardyHostArtFlemingWithContestants.png"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Gilbert Shelton" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 17:11:52 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Freewheelin Franklin of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fabulous_Furry_Freak_Brothers&quot;&gt;Fabulous Furry Freak Brothers&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Wed, 20 Apr 2022 17:11:57 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/20/freewheelinFranklin.png"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 19" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2022 13:12:16 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="19">
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yHEojamzcTE&quot;&gt;That's Amore&lt;/a&gt;." created="Tue, 19 Apr 2022 14:42:40 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Wearing a mask is like not taking a shit in public, but worse, because the shit won't give people a &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_COVID&quot;&gt;horrible disease&lt;/a&gt; for the rest of their lives. How hard is that to understand?" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2022 19:05:47 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="That feeling when I take a guess at how something complicated might work, just to get something started that I can debug, only to find it works without any problems as-is. " created="Tue, 19 Apr 2022 14:18:23 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I don't guess at &lt;a href=&quot;http://daytona.scripting.com/?q=wordle&amp;collection=scriptingnews&quot;&gt;Wordle&lt;/a&gt;. I have an algorithm. But then I'm a programmer, so what did you expect? :smile:" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2022 13:12:17 GMT" type="outline"/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 18" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 14:12:40 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="18">
				<outline text="We're going to need curated lists of feeds, like people do curated lists of Twitter users. If we're going to make the most of the coming reboot of &quot;RSS&quot;, we should be prepared to help people get the immediate benefit without doing a lot of upfront work. Having wonderfully thoughtful collections of feeds, based on real expertise, would be a great welcome wagon for new users. I can help with the presentation. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 20:49:23 GMT" type="outline" image="http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2009/05/06/loverss.gif" imageLink="http://scripting.com/stories/2009/05/06/rssIsDeadMyAss.html"/>
				<outline text="OMG -- &lt;i&gt;two&lt;/i&gt; episodes of &lt;a href=&quot;http://daytona.scripting.com/?q=better%20call%20saul&amp;collection=scriptingnews&quot;&gt;Better Call Saul&lt;/a&gt; tonight, and &lt;i&gt;three&lt;/i&gt; NBA playoff games. I have never been so gifted by quality entertainment. And my software development is going well, last week's stagnation has given way to this week's steady progress. I needed a break obviously. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 20:18:48 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="There's a new trend in journalism where editors &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1516093318974824449&quot;&gt;turn away from Twitter&lt;/a&gt;, thinking of it as a waste of time. Another theory is that this is where the news happens and turning away from Twitter would be like a journalist of the 80s turning off their phone." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 17:04:40 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="No &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/10/us/politics/crypto-industry-states-legislation.html?unlocked_article_code=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACEIPuomT1JKd6J17Vw1cRCfTTMQmqxCdw_PIxftm3iWka3DJDm8aiPkORJCH_0bRZKF4INApziyHQ5pANrMyX-Bo36pEI0VxRhLtppaLmY8BKjk0roT1Xn8z29iFe4EExgLQTzvzLvZjlvr4tgiaMTO0DLqO1HxwIwg2o49kdl7-xXB&quot;&gt;wonder&lt;/a&gt; so many &lt;a href=&quot;https://news.crunchbase.com/news/florida-miami-startups-vc-investment/&quot;&gt;VCs are moving to Florida&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 14:18:38 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I hear they're adding &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/tv/we-regret-to-inform-you-that-tucker-carlsons-new-special-does-in-fact-promote-testicle-tanning/&quot;&gt;testicle tanning&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnn.com/2022/04/17/us/florida-math-textbooks-critical-race-theory/index.html&quot;&gt;Florida math textbooks&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 14:16:29 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Martin&quot;&gt;George Martin&lt;/a&gt; is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monosodium_glutamate&quot;&gt;MSG&lt;/a&gt; of the Beatles. The flavor comes from the song and the performance four Beatles. But the music grabs you harder because of Martin's chemistry. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 16:23:57 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="You know the old question -- if a troll trolls in a forest and no one's listening are they still trolling? The answer is no." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 14:12:41 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Site licenses" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:14:12 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="In 1986, my little software company was in a weird place. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:14:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We had a great product almost ready to ship for the Mac. Everyone was psyched, MacUser and MacWorld, the people inside Apple, the people we leaked it to in the industry. But we were broke, couldn't make payroll. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:14:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="My board was tired of the roller coaster, they told me to shut the company down. I told them they were crazy, we're sitting on the best product anyone has ever made, and the market is totally ready for it. The Mac was finally selling in huge numbers, after they fixed all the problems, and most other software devs were shutting down their mac development in the year before, we were going to have the booming mac software market virtually to ourselves. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:15:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="No deal. The board wouldn't put up the $400K we needed to get to shipping the product. So I went to my best friend at Apple, and told him what was going on. We were going to have to shut down before shipping the product you want so badly. I begged for their help. Man did they help us. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:16:15 GMT"/>
					<outline text="First they gave us the money we needed to stay open as a loan. We had to put the source code to the product in escrow. We also did a second deal. They bought a site license for the product, everyone at Apple would get a copy, and in return they'd give us 40 new Mac systems with lots of memory, printers, networking. And they gave us 10 more Macs to give to our board members, which was also really smart. None of them had Macs." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:16:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The reason I told this story is the power of the site license. I would have paid them all to use the product, because once the hardware company is standardizing on your product, you'll never go out of business as long as they're in business. And the inverse was true too. If we all had Macs maybe we'd stop thinking about making software for PCs. Back then Apple had guts and smarts. Quite a combo. Probably because they too had gone through tough times and were emerging from them. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 21:17:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It was the best year of my life in the software world, and I've had some good years. ;-)"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 17" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 13:05:12 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="17">
				<outline text="Om Malik's &lt;a href=&quot;https://om.co/2022/04/15/musk-or-not-twitter-ceo-needs-to-go/&quot;&gt;must-read&lt;/a&gt; on the full picture at Twitter. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:19:29 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="From watching Severance twice, I now know why, when Helly goes out through the exit, trying to escape, she immediately comes back through the same door she went out from. It wasn't metaphysical. There's a simple explanation for it. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 03:59:27 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Tell someone they did something good, or they look nice, or they're a great friend. Or give them something nice to eat. I just realized it's so rare that we do this. Everyone's looking for a nice word of praise or reassurance. We treat our pets better than our human friends." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 13:05:13 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="A more concise brain dump" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 16:12:55 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Key point -- Twitter has been going nowhere for its whole life, just drifting, aimlessly." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 16:13:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The companies Musk leads do not drift. They create amazing products that change things. "/>
					<outline text="The way we need Twitter to change." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 16:13:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1515721884461146119&quot;&gt;full thread&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 16:13:38 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Let a thousand Twitters bloom" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:24:58 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="A rambling brain dump about Twitter and Musk." created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 03:43:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Self-moderation is going to be a huge deal. Maybe something like self-driving Teslas. Which the driver controls, btw. It isn't a passive thing. If a Musk company can do that, yeah I think they can give users more control over the bullshit they have to deal with on Twitter. The thing is Twitter has been stuck since 2006 when it started. They hired people to make the system run reliably, which is fantastic, hat's off, but it needs a few more things to be able to realizae its potential as a world-scale notification system for all kinds of networked writing. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:25:07 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Maybe to make something workable you have to start something new, not in a half assed way.. Or maybe a no-bullshit capitalist like Musk can make it come about from the chaos of Twitter." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:25:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Most people have no idea how software works and is made. " created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 03:27:49 GMT" type="outline"/>
					<outline text="A Twitter-like webservice at &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Web_Services&quot;&gt;AWS&lt;/a&gt;. With better docs and a JavaScript API that doesn't require developer to run a server (big deal). Effortless install on Digital Ocean." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:25:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Let a thousand Twitters bloom." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:31:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Interop baked in from the beginning." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:25:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Look, Elon made buying a car a completely online experience, moving around huge amounts of money and metal and an explosion in demand. Buying a Tesla was like buying a Mac in 1984 or an iPhone in 2007, except they're doing it 365 days a year for years. And buying a StarLink is just as easy and just as much of a sensation. If this is easy to do why do so few companies do it?" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:26:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="BTW, if Musk was trying to buy my bank, I'd be all for it. That's how bad their software is. All banks have shit software, btw, near as I can tell. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:27:15 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Seriously, if you think he can't run Twitter when he can run StarLink and Tesla, please. And why should Twitter be stuck in the mud like it has been since inception. It desperately needs some fixes, and at a minumum must be made easier to peer with. Developers can do all the work if they just add a few simple features that they probably already have implemented. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:27:35 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I was an Apple dev in 1997 when Jobs came back. Musk is like Jobs in that he won't be scared to make the big changes that are needed. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:28:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="We're lucky a guy like Musk is hanging around and willing to take on this job. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:30:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And as usual the journalists see a teeny little corner of the picture and are screaming about that. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:30:56 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Diego Rivera" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:37:05 GMT" type="outline" metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/17/theMilliner.png">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.diego-rivera-foundation.org/The-Milliner-Potrait-Of-Henri-De-Chatillon-1944.html&quot;&gt;The Milliner. Potrait of Henri de Chatillon&lt;/a&gt;, 1944." created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 15:37:18 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/17/theMilliner.png"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 16" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2022 15:34:22 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="16">
				<outline text="Another great Peloton song -- &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eFTLKWw542g&quot;&gt;We Didn't Start The Fire&lt;/a&gt; by Billy Joel." created="Sat, 16 Apr 2022 22:48:33 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="If you liked &lt;a href=&quot;http://daytona.scripting.com/?q=severance&amp;collection=scriptingnews&quot;&gt;Severance&lt;/a&gt; but have only seen it once, watch it again. I found there were a lot of things that only made sense when you'd seen it all the way through. And I missed a bunch of stuff the first time around. " created="Sun, 17 Apr 2022 03:42:08 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Twitter could use the smarts of my Tesla Model 3. It could let me do moderation for myself the same way I tell my car how I want it to drive. " created="Sat, 16 Apr 2022 15:34:23 GMT" type="outline"/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 15" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 14:35:02 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="15">
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RaYfA7tfT1g&quot;&gt;Bertha&lt;/a&gt; may be the best song to &lt;a href=&quot;http://daytona.scripting.com/?q=peloton&amp;collection=scriptingnews&quot;&gt;Peloton&lt;/a&gt; to. &quot;That's why, if you please, Bertha don't you come round here any more.&quot;" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:04:56 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Like many fans of the Grateful Dead I thought Bertha was about a fan in the Dead office named Bertha, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dead.net/features/greatest-stories-ever-told/greatest-stories-ever-told-bertha&quot;&gt;but&lt;/a&gt; it's the other way around, the fan was given the name of the song. On the other hand, the Beatles song, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RXawa90YU2s&quot;&gt;Martha My Dear&lt;/a&gt; &lt;i&gt;is&lt;/i&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martha_My_Dear&quot;&gt;about&lt;/a&gt; Paul McCartney's Old English Sheepdog &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/search?q=martha+mccartney&quot;&gt;Martha&lt;/a&gt;. Speaking of McCartney, I learned recently that he co-wrote the fantastic Elvis Costello song &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g-rF4COOd9c&quot;&gt;Veronica&lt;/a&gt;. It's definitely got the McCartney feel to it, another spin perhaps on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HuS5NuXRb5Y&quot;&gt;Eleanor Rigby&lt;/a&gt;, which is &lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; a good song to Peloton to, btw, imho. " created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:12:05 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/15/theEggman.png"/>
				<outline text="I love all the Beatles songs, but get the most, these days, out of John Lennon's songs. I learned that Lennon only partially completed his songs, leaving a lot of the work to &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Martin&quot;&gt;George Martin&lt;/a&gt;. Keep that in mind when you listen to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1Jm5epJr10&quot;&gt;I Am The Walrus&lt;/a&gt; (my favorite Beatles song) and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HtUH9z_Oey8&quot;&gt;Strawberry Fields&lt;/a&gt;, as examples. The orchestral bits are pure Martin. " created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:21:14 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I have the best &lt;a href=&quot;http://daytona.scripting.com/?q=daytona&amp;collection=scriptingnews&quot;&gt;search engine&lt;/a&gt; for a blog. I'm sure there's better search software out there, but no one else has the sheer quantity of blog-writing over so much time in a searchable index. There are bits missing here and there, and I'm determined to fill those bits in -- but the archive goes from October 7, 1994 at 11:27AM to the present day. A lot of stuff happened in that time, and some of it happened right &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. I hope someday it proves to be a useful resource to people studying this period, with the usual caveat, assuming the human species survives. :smile:" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:18:58 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Because the weather has been delightful here the last few days, I'm afraid I got no work done this week. I basically gave up today and spent time in the sun, reading, listening to music, went for a walk, did some shopping, took a long nap in the afternoon. I guess I was overdue for some downtime. It is a wonderful time of year, winter truly is over. We will still get some coldish weather, no doubt, but the glory of &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catskill_Mountains&quot;&gt;Catskills&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fuz5TKzaJoE&quot;&gt;summer&lt;/a&gt; is coming soon. It's the &lt;i&gt;best&lt;/i&gt; place to be in the summer. " created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:00:44 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="If Twitter had peered with other Twitter-like systems then they never would have had to develop and pay for content moderation. It's *possible* this is factored into Musk's plan. File this under &quot;silos are expensive to run.&quot;" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 18:33:48 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="One more thing -- the NBA Playoffs are here! And while my Knicks are not in contention this year, it does have the feel of an unusually good year. One reason it's so cool, no &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.si.com/nba/2022/04/06/lakers-eliminated-from-playoff-contention-suns-loss&quot;&gt;LeBron James&lt;/a&gt;! Hopefully at some point he'll stop trying to form superteams and finish his career with humility and grace, away from contention. I am rooting for teams with stars who have never won a championship, notably the Phoenix Suns and &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Paul&quot;&gt;Chris Paul&lt;/a&gt;. I'm also glad to see the Warriors are back in the mix with the same big three and no Kevin Durant, who I will be rooting &lt;i&gt;against&lt;/i&gt; every time he takes the court. I hope Boston blows the Nets out so that embarassment for the great city of New York is over for another year. Maybe they want him back in Oklahoma? I'm interested to see if James Harden can get it together to have a good long run, and while he has never won a championship, hmmm, I don't know. He played on the Nets this year, and for that reason I question his motivations. I do not like artificially created superteams designed to win championships. And of course they rarely do. So hopefully that chapter of the NBA will be over. One thing for sure &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2016/07/09/1363.html&quot;&gt;sports is not arithmetic&lt;/a&gt;, esp not basketball." created="Fri, 15 Apr 2022 22:35:15 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/15/cp3.png"/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="April 14" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:39:38 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="14">
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1514587047901675524&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Drummer is different, it's not like Blogger or Movable Type or my own Radio UserLand, from the early 00s.&quot;" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 21:38:15 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="When I switched from a Pixel 4a to an iPhone 13, I didn't realize that Google's Messages app didn't work on iOS, which is causing me all kinds of grief. This stuff doesn't work, basically." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 21:13:32 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="A copy of &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/14/muskLetterToTwitter.png&quot;&gt;Musk's letter&lt;/a&gt; to Twitter management. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 15:01:51 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Musk's Twitter, first comments" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:39:39 GMT" type="outline" metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/14/elonMusk.png" description="There are reasons to be optimistic about Musk's Twitter, if that comes to be.">
					<outline text="There are reasons to be optimistic about &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-04-14/elon-musk-offers-to-buy-twitter-for-54-20-a-share&quot;&gt;Musk's Twitter&lt;/a&gt;, if &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2022/04/14/muskLetterToTwitter.png&quot;&gt;that&lt;/a&gt; comes to be. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:39:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="For one thing, none of the CEOs of Twitter going back to the beginning were &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/stories/2009/11/24/naturalbornBlogger.html&quot;&gt;natural bloggers&lt;/a&gt;. Musk is." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="When he was joining the board, I thought that was good because having a user on the board of a tech company is pretty unusual, and would be a good thing. Having a user as the CEO -- even better. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:13 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Also there's too much religion in the UI of Twitter. Musk's ideas have been pragmatic. On the right path, imho." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I am a customer of Tesla and StarLink, and both companies appear to be run well, and what they do is imho harder than running Twitter, which basically is the kind of service the tech industry is good at running." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="My main concern with Musk as the new owner of Twitter is that Trump will be back. I think it was proven beyond any doubt that Twitter can be grossly misused, and the company has to be ready to stop its service from being used in such a harmful way." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Free speech is not an absolute -- the old Shouting &lt;i&gt;fire&lt;/i&gt; in a crowded movie theater &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shouting_fire_in_a_crowded_theater&quot;&gt;idea&lt;/a&gt;. Trump used Twitter to organize the overthrow of the US government and almost succeeded at it." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I am also concerned that Musk will curtail the Twitter API, which is incredibly useful and under-exploited by the company and its users. I've built a lot of tech on top of the API, and would miss it if it were gone." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:40:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="BTW, I am a shareholder of Twitter and would prefer to continue to hold my stock. I was holding it as a long-term investment. Not interested in selling it at this time. Was hoping for a much larger return.  " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:43:18 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Just some early morning thoughts on this topic, sure to be much discussed. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 12:41:05 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;b&gt;Update #1&lt;/b&gt;" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:01:53 GMT"/>
					<outline text="A reader asked why I was concerned that Musk might curtail the Twitter API. Basically, because I've seen things like that happen over and over in Silicon Valley." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:01:56 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="I've been through this before with Apple. When Steve Jobs returned he shut down Mac internet devs, by bundling open source versions of what our products did, somewhat. Enough to kill our markets. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:02:25 GMT"/>
						<outline text="When a new owner comes in and finds projects with serious staff that aren't generating revenue and have no clear purpose, they at least think about dropping them. Great example, again with Steve Jobs -- not that I disagree with what he cut, he just made huge cuts in some things that were really good and unique for a tech company, like their internal library. Most of what he cut were boondoggles, some of which competed with independent products that were better than Apple's. In other words they were spending money to hold back the market. Foolish. " created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:02:35 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="&lt;b&gt;Update #2&lt;/b&gt;" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:50:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="FWIW, I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2017/01/14/whatIfTwtrIsBoughtByARepub.html&quot;&gt;warned in 2017&lt;/a&gt; that Twitter's price was too low, and that a Republican backer like Shelly Adelson or the Koch Brothers could buy it and make it run like Fox News. It's a good thing they didn't because for sure Trump would still be using Twitter to organize his coup." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:50:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="People who responded said it'd never happen because Twitter's balance sheet was too weak to justify an acquisition. They missed that not all of Twitter's value shows up on its balance sheet." created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 14:50:46 GMT"/>
					</outline>
