				<outline text="People get really pissy about Elon Musk. Why do they care so much? Such angst. His rockets work. I love the cars they make. Just ordered Skylink. There hasn't been a person since Steve Jobs who could get me to buy all their ideas. I respect that, even if you don't like him. ;-)" created="Tue, 05 Apr 2022 16:12:45 GMT" type="outline" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1511373919210647559"/>
				<outline text="I gave a talk at a class at CUNY yesterday and did an &lt;a href=&quot;http://this.how/cunyClassNotes/&quot;&gt;outline&lt;/a&gt; beforehand. I didn’t need to refer to it, because outlining it put the structure in my mind, and I could work from that as I lectured." created="Tue, 05 Apr 2022 13:46:37 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/5/23011256/elon-musk-twitter-board-of-directors-ownership&quot;&gt;News today&lt;/a&gt; that Elon Musk has been named to the Twitter board. There's a fair amount of angst about this but he &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1511341423198670857&quot;&gt;might&lt;/a&gt; be really good for it. He's actually made software, himself -- and presumably knows how to write a bug report. And he uses the product. I don't imagine too many of the other board members at Twitter really use it. Leadership from users, what a concept." created="Tue, 05 Apr 2022 13:55:46 GMT" type="outline"/>
